 Security beefed up for first ODI
OUR CORRESPONDENTGuwahati: Unprecedented security has been organised for Mondays India-Pakistan one-day International at the Nehru Stadium here. There were security personnel seen in every nook and corner of the stadium and its surrounding areas. The team hotels also resembled fortresses. In the morning, Army personnel with sniffer dogs checked out the playing arena. It was followed by a meeting between Match Referee Roshan Mahanama, DIG G.P. Singh, City SSP Surendra Kumar and ACA officials, who said that the former Sri Lanka batsman was satisfied with the security arrangement. Said Kamrup (Metropolitan) deputy commissioner Avinash Joshi, We have taken all possible measures to ensure a smooth game. Lessons from the crowd trouble at the last ODI have been learnt. Besides security personnel in uniform, we also have an invisible security ring. 
